---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const personJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Prem',
  url: 'https://my-blog-kohl-one.vercel.app/about',
  jobTitle: 'Solo Entrepreneur',
  description: 'Building VerdeX Farm — a smart hydroponic system for commercial herb growers. Writing about entrepreneurship, hydroponics, and technology.',
  address: {
    '@type': 'PostalAddress',
    addressLocality: 'Chiang Mai',
    addressCountry: 'TH',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="I'm Prem — a solo entrepreneur in Chiang Mai, Thailand, building VerdeX Farm and writing about the journey."
  jsonLd={personJsonLd}
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-6">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900/40 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-8 h-8 text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400" viewBox="0 0 32 32" fill="currentColor">
            <path d="M16 28 C16 28 16 14 16 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none"/>
            <path d="M16 20 C16 20 10 17 9 11 C9 11 15 11 16 20Z" opacity="0.9"/>
            <path d="M16 16 C16 16 22 12 23 6 C23 6 17 8 16 16Z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-50 mb-1">About Me</h1>
          <p class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400">Solo entrepreneur · Chiang Mai, Thailand</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bio content -->
    <div class="prose-content">
      <p>
        สวัสดีครับ — I'm <strong>Prem</strong>, a solo entrepreneur based in Chiang Mai, Thailand.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm building <a href="#">VerdeX Farm</a> — a smart hydroponic system designed for commercial
        herb growers in Southeast Asia. It started as a rooftop experiment with lettuce and Thai basil,
        and has grown into something I think about every waking hour.
      </p>

      <h2>What I do</h2>

      <p>
        My work sits at the intersection of <strong>agriculture</strong>, <strong>technology</strong>,
        and <strong>entrepreneurship</strong>. I design nutrient film technique (NFT) systems, write
        the firmware that controls them, and figure out how to make the economics work for small-to-medium
        herb farms across the region.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before going solo, I worked in tech — but the pull toward building something physical, something
        that grows, was too strong to ignore.
      </p>

      <h2>Why I write</h2>

      <p>
        This blog is my way of thinking out loud. Building a company alone can be isolating, and writing
        forces a kind of clarity that staying in your head never does. I write about:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong> — the solo kind, without investors or co-founders</li>
        <li><strong>Hydroponics</strong> — what works, what doesn't, and what I'm learning</li>
        <li><strong>Technology</strong> — tools I use, ideas I find interesting</li>
        <li><strong>Building in public</strong> — honest notes, no polish</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>About Chiang Mai</h2>

      <p>
        I chose Chiang Mai because it offers the space to do slow, deliberate work. The cost of living
        is reasonable, the community is warm, and there's something about the pace here that makes it
        easier to focus on what matters. Mountains help too.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>

      <p>
        I'd love to hear from you — whether you're working on something similar, have questions about
        hydroponics, or just want to say hi.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="/contact">Send me a message</a> or find me on the links in the footer.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
